      "result": "# Expiration Date - Legal Review Required\n\nBased on my analysis of the provided contract document, here are the relevant parts related to **\"Expiration Date\"** that should be reviewed by a lawyer:\n\n## Key Contract Term Definition:\n\n**\"Term\" Definition (Page 2):**\n> \"Term\" means the earlier of: (a) the end of the two year period from the Effective Date to 31 July 2013; or (b) the last day of the calendar month within which the Maximum Distribution Commitment is reached.\"\n\n## Critical Details for Legal Review:\n\n1. **Initial Term Expiration Date: July 31, 2013**\n   - The contract explicitly states the initial term will expire on **31 July 2013** (assuming this is two years from the Effective Date)\n\n2. **Alternative Termination Trigger:**\n   - The contract may terminate earlier if the \"Maximum Distribution Commitment\" is reached before July 31, 2013\n   - The expiration would then be \"the last day of the calendar month within which the Maximum Distribution Commitment is reached\"\n\n3. **Ambiguity Requiring Legal Attention:**\n   - The Maximum Distribution Commitment is defined as \"[* ]\" (redacted), making it impossible to assess when this alternative termination condition might be triggered\n   - A lawyer should review whether this early termination provision is favorable to your interests\n\n## Recommendation:\nA lawyer should carefully review:\n- The actual Maximum Distribution Commitment amount (currently redacted)\n- Whether automatic renewal provisions exist (not visible in provided excerpt)\n- Notice requirements for non-renewal or termination",
